title: Facebook has hired the professor who Johns Hopkins fired after he stormed a building occupied by protesters
text: Facebook told CNBC it has hired Daniel Povey, a speech recognition researcher who was fired this week from John Hopkins University.

title: Avoid names associated with China, look at software, internet stocks: Alpha One's Niles
text: Dan Niles, Alpha One Capital founding partner, joins CNBC's "Closing Bell" to discuss semiconductor stocks and President Donald Trump's additional proposed tariffs.

title: Facebook denies giving contradictory evidence to parliament
text: Committee chairman suggested staff knew Cambridge Analytica had misused data

title: Why Facebook Is Shortening the Leash on Its Top Apps
text: The social media giant revealed earlier this month that it will attach its name to a pair of its top-performing subsidiary apps, Instagram and WhatsApp.

title: Facebook Wants to Become a Source for "Trustworthy News"
text: The social media giant is working on a dedicated news section with premium content.

title: Goldman Sachs: Service Stocks will Win the Trade War
text: Investors should consider services-providing stocks as opposed to goods-producing stocks amid an ongoing trade war that is unlikely to end soon.

title: Facebook reportedly ditched plans to buy a social networking competitor over antitrust fears
text: Facebook reportedly considered acquiring video chat app Houseparty, but it abandoned the deal due to concerns around heightened antitrust scrutiny.

title: How Facebook Is Changing to Deal With Scrutiny of Its Power
text: In both pre-emptive and defensive ways, the social network is modifying its behavior to fend off antitrust concerns.
